      • getTimeStamp

        long getTimeStamp()
        Returns the time at which the request was first created. Consumers of the result of this request can use this time to determine if their cached results are still valid.

        If the result of the request has been cached to disk, then the time returned from this method should be the time the request whose data was cached to disk was created. In other words, data cached to disk should contain the time stamp.

        This method should return before the results of the request are available.

        This method is used to propagate invalidations when using on disk caches containing request results from a previously run java process.

        Returns:
        A long value representing the time the request was created, measured in milliseconds since the epoch (00:00:00 GMT, January 1, 1970).
